description:
Visual Studio 2022 is open with the ChemCalc solution. The project directory contains a dataset 'elements.csv'. Your goal is to use a T4 Text Template to parse this CSV at design time and generate a C# class with constants. Create a Text Template in the ChemCalc project named 'ElementConstants.tt' containing the following code:

<#@ template debug="false" hostspecific="true" language="C#" #>
<#@ assembly name="System.Core" #>
<#@ import namespace="System.IO" #>
<#@ import namespace="System.Collections.Generic" #>
<#@ output extension=".cs" #>
namespace ChemCalc
{
    public static class ElementConstants
    {
<#
        string path = this.Host.ResolvePath("elements.csv");
        if (File.Exists(path))
        {
            string[] lines = File.ReadAllLines(path);
            for(int i = 1; i < lines.Length; i++)
            {
                string[] parts = lines[i].Split(',');
                if(parts.Length >= 4)
                {
                    string name = parts[2].Trim();
                    string mass = parts[3].Trim();
#>
        public const double <#= name #> = <#= mass #>;
<#
                }
            }
        }
#>
    }
}

Generate the 'ElementConstants.cs' file from the template. In 'Program.cs', uncomment the line 'Console.WriteLine($"Carbon Mass: {ElementConstants.Carbon}");' and ensure the solution builds successfully without errors.
